<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1304,1547]" box="[151,558,1304,1331]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,1304,1331]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1304,1547]" box="[199,1122,1340,1368]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1340,1367]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe, except for the south. 
<collectingCountry box="[690,789,1341,1367]" name="Portugal" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: one province (Beira Litoral).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1304,1547]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1377,1403]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Ecology.</emphasis>
The only Portuguese specimen was collected in a pine forest with 
<taxonomicName box="[1047,1180,1377,1403]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1047,1125,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Acacia</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1192,1355,1377,1403]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Arbutus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="unedo">
<emphasis box="[1192,1355,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Arbutus unedo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Quercus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P.Miller" authorityYear="1768" box="[296,476,1413,1439]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sativa">
<emphasis box="[296,476,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Castanea sativa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity box="[491,567,1413,1439]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="m" value="700.0">700 m</quantity>
). In northwestern Europe, it clearly prefers mature moderately humid deciduous forests (
<bibRefCitation author="Pollet, M." box="[286,421,1449,1475]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref34362" refString="Pollet, M. (2000) A documented Red List of the dolichopodid flies (Diptera: Dolichopodidae) of Flanders [in Dutch with English summary]. Communications of the Institute of Nature Conservation, 8, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="2000">Pollet 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1304,1547]" box="[199,638,1484,1511]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1484,1511]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
1.1 (very rare). Rare (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1304,1547]" box="[199,445,1520,1547]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,1520,1547]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Activity period.</emphasis>
July.
</paragraph>
